text.tspan: - AXI Slave Lite : through this interface it receives read and write
commands and their respective addresses from CPU
- AXI Master : thorugh this interface it directly accesses the DRAM
(or the cache of the cpu if we are connected to ACP) and then it reads
the data (if the command which has arrived from the CPU is an EMMC write
command) or it writes the data if the command which has arrived from
the CPU is an EMMC read command.
There is an interrupt line from the AXI EMMC controller to the CPU.
Whenever processing of a command arrived from CPU is finished
the module will inform the CPU about the situation.
so that the CPU can issue the next command.
